org.mitre.provenance.surrogate

Class Surrogateable

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.mitre.provenance.surrogate.Surrogateable
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    PLUSObject

    public abstract class Surrogateable
extends Object
    Represents and object that can either be a surrogate, or have surrogates generated for it. A surrogate is an alternate version of a provenance object, usually with less information, that is releasable to someone with fewer permissions than are required to see the full object.
    Author:
    DMALLEN

      • useSurrogateComputation

        public void useSurrogateComputation(SurrogateGeneratingFunction sgf)
        Use this method to "attach" a surrogate computation function to a data item. When surrogates are needed, this computation function will be used. It should be an instance of class SurrogateGeneratingFunction.

        More than one SGF can be used for a class, so call this as many times as you want, but with different computation classes.

        Parameters:
        sgf - the function to use to calculate.
        See Also:
        SurrogateGeneratingFunction
